                    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

Please try again later.Jodytek5.0 out of 5 stars Entry Level home studio drum mic kit Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2020Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase This is a great set of drum mics for a entry level home studio setup. The build quality is good, and they sound great. My setup is this set of mic, with a tascam US-16X08 USB interface and Logic Pro. I invested in a couple Pyle boom stands to get the overheads.Recordings are what you would expect for using a spare bedroom as a drum room. There a definite dynamic ranges and cross bleeding. But for less than $500 for an entire setup, it's definitely worth it. I believe you could spend a lot more money for Shure or other major brands, and only have incrementally better sound, in the given studio space.I would recommend spending your money on the better audio interface, daw, and sound dampening for your space. Read more Helpful Report abuse Landon Cunningham5.0 out of 5 stars Great, low-cost mics Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2015Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase I use these mics primarily to rehearse in my home studio. They are great for what I use them for. The sound quality is not as good as expensive mics but if you're looking simply to amplify the sound on a budget then these are great mics. Sturdy construction. The only downside, you have to really tighten the snare and tom mics. Mine tend to move easily ; whether because of a heavy cable pulling them down or from when I hit the drums very hard. I wouldn't use these to record something that I needed to sound super professional (though they could work) but I definitely will use them for live gigs. Read more One person found this helpful Helpful Report abuse LMB4.0 out of 5 stars Overall, a good purchase Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2015Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase Great price and shipping was on time. Mics are good quality and the built on clips make this an extra good deal. They are easy to install and move around. Some reviews have complained about the size, but I have no problem with them. I played with them on for a bit before plugging them in to get used to the size and not hitting them. They sound good. Quality is not amazing, but for the price it can’t be beat. The condenser mics are good for my needs and the kick is pretty good. I also added an SM58 to the kick as well and mixing down both mics together gave me a pretty good sound. Overall, pleased with the purchase. Read more One person found this helpful Helpful Report abuse RegularJoe5.0 out of 5 stars Great Bang for the Buck! Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2018Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase Needed mic's for an outdoor gig in a pinch. Didn't have a lot to spend. Was initially concerned about the quality when ordering, but figured something is better than nothing. I am very pleased with them. Didn't seem 'cheap' at all. did the job very well; everyone was impressed with the sound. Read more Helpful Report abuse Jamie DeMello5.0 out of 5 stars Great Mics Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2021Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase The mics are great, and what makes it even better is that it didn’t break the bank either! I wish their mics weren’t as bulky, but for the price, they are very durable. And the sound is fantastic. Read more Helpful Report abuse drum095.0 out of 5 stars Well worth the $$ Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2012Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase CAD D10 Bass kick mic has the deep low thump needed for live shows. The D29's do the job for your toms $ snare with easy mounting design and stay there!! the C9's are phantom powered which makes them very sensitive to the highs from cymbals providing the chrisp sharp response in the mix from my drum kit. Over all these are well worth the less than $200.00 price tag, I actualy spent $160.00 here on amazon with shipping. I find if you place items in the wish list the price will change from time to time and you be told when you log on. Landon Cunningham5.0 out of 5 stars Great, low-cost mics Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2015Style: 7-Piece Drum PackVerified Purchase I use these mics primarily to rehearse in my home studio. They are great for what I use them for. The sound quality is not as good as expensive mics but if you're looking simply to amplify the sound on a budget then these are great mics. Sturdy construction. The only downside, you have to really tighten the snare and tom mics. Mine tend to move easily ; whether because of a heavy cable pulling them down or from when I hit the drums very hard. I wouldn't use these to record something that I needed to sound super professional (though they could work) but I definitely will use them for live gigs.
